    <title>Build an ecommerce website with React and Django (1)</title>
    <link href="http://wonderdaystudio.com/2020/04/06/2020-04-07-Build%20an%20ecommerce%20website%20with%20React%20and%20Django/"/>
    <id>http://wonderdaystudio.com/2020/04/06/2020-04-07-Build%20an%20ecommerce%20website%20with%20React%20and%20Django/</id>
    <published>2020-04-07T02:21:29.000Z</published>
    <updated>2020-05-30T00:43:24.745Z</updated>
    
    <summary type="html">
    
      &lt;p&gt;I start learning full-stack development by building an eCommerce website with React and Django.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/wonderyue/Autocart&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Project Repository&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://autocart.rj.r.appspot.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Features:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;authentication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;product list&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;cart&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;order history&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;rating and comment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;edit mode for administrator&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is the first one of a serial of articles, and I’d like to talk about things I should know earlier.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;Packages-Lifesavers-I-should-know-earlier&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Packages-Lifesavers-I-should-know-earlier&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Packages(Lifesavers) I should know earlier&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Packages(Lifesavers) I should know earlier&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id=&quot;1-react-moment&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#1-react-moment&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;1. react-moment&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;1. react-moment&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;!-- [react-moment](https://www.npmjs.com/package/react-moment) --&gt;
&lt;p&gt;  I use DateTimeField in Django model, and it saved as a string like “2020-04-11T18:36:05.748Z” in database. It is hard to display it in the frontend. I add another read-only field when serializing the model, convert the DateTimeField value to timestamp. And create a Date object in the frontend. Then, I find this package, and revert what I have done…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;  And it is also useful when you need to display “post a minute/two days ago” in a comment or feed component.&lt;/p&gt;
    
    </summary>
    
    
